<subSubSection id="C322B4E76665FFD5FF0B03776C6C9E6B" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6665FFD5FF0B037769D79D27" blockId="3.[151,1437,1127,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FF0B0377696F9C93" bold="true" box="[151,305,1127,1154]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species has predominantly been reported from 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6665FFD5FCE603786BE59C93" box="[890,955,1128,1154]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Texas</collectingRegion>
waters with a few individuals from coastal waters of 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6665FFD5FE95039C69299CB7" box="[265,375,1164,1190]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6665FFD5FE2C039C6A5B9CB7" box="[432,517,1164,1190]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Florida</collectingRegion>
. The waters of the southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F32FA7FC6665FFD5FCE9039C6BF99CB7" box="[885,935,1164,1190]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">U.S.</collectingCountry>
are on the northern periphery of the natural range of this species and individuals captured historically in the waters of the northern GOM, predominantly off 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6665FFD5FF0B03C468859CFF" box="[151,219,1236,1262]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Texas</collectingRegion>
, were likely transient individuals utilizing these waters during warmer months of the year. However, there are no recent records of this species from the northern GOM, indicating it may have been extirpated from the region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FF03020C69239D27" author="Burgess, G. H. &amp; Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L." box="[159,381,1308,1334]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref16190" refString="Burgess, G. H., Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L. (2009) An evaluation of the status of the largetooth sawfish, Pristis perotteti, based on historic and recent distribution and qualitative observations of abundance. Florida Museum of Natural History Report, 2009, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="2009">
Burgess 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FE9D020C69649D27" box="[257,314,1308,1334]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6665FFD5FF5B022F6C6C9E6B" blockId="3.[151,1437,1127,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FF5B022F698B9D4B" bold="true" box="[199,469,1343,1370]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
A rostrum collected prior to 1878 and deposited in the Ichthyology Collection at the Academy of Natural Sciences in 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6665FFD5FD9B02746ACD9D6F" box="[519,659,1380,1406]" country="Jordan" name="'Amman" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Philadelphia</collectingRegion>
(ANSP 17388; listed as 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6665FFD5FC3902746C1D9D6C" authorityName="Latham" authorityYear="1794" box="[933,1091,1380,1405]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Pristidae" genus="Pristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pristiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="antiquorum">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FC3902746C1D9D6C" box="[933,1091,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">P. antiquorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but verified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6665FFD5FB6C02746D0F9D6C" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1264,1361,1380,1405]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Squalidae" genus="Squalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squaliformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pristis">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FB6C02746D0F9D6C" box="[1264,1361,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">P. pristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is the first verified record of this species in the GOM (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FD2D02986BD09DB3" author="Burgess, G. H. &amp; Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L." box="[689,910,1416,1442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref16190" refString="Burgess, G. H., Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L. (2009) An evaluation of the status of the largetooth sawfish, Pristis perotteti, based on historic and recent distribution and qualitative observations of abundance. Florida Museum of Natural History Report, 2009, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="2009">
Burgess 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FC8F02986B129DB3" box="[787,844,1416,1442]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
), although it is not clear where in the GOM the specimen originated. Many previous records of sawfish originating from the 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6665FFD5FC6902BC6C689DD7" box="[1013,1078,1452,1478]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Texas</collectingRegion>
coast could refer to this species as it has been suggested that the ratio of 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6665FFD5FDC502C06AE49DF8" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[601,698,1488,1513]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Squalidae" genus="Squalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squaliformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pristis">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FDC502C06AE49DF8" box="[601,698,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">P. pristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6665FFD5FD4102C06B3E9DF8" authorityName="Latham" authorityYear="1794" box="[733,864,1488,1513]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Pristidae" genus="Pristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pristiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FD4102C06B3E9DF8" box="[733,864,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">P. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the area was historically around 1:1, but none of these records could be verified (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FE6702E46A899E1F" author="Burgess, G. H. &amp; Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L." box="[507,727,1524,1550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref16190" refString="Burgess, G. H., Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L. (2009) An evaluation of the status of the largetooth sawfish, Pristis perotteti, based on historic and recent distribution and qualitative observations of abundance. Florida Museum of Natural History Report, 2009, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="2009">
Burgess 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FDC002E46ACA9E1F" box="[604,660,1524,1550]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). The mention of this species (as 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6665FFD5FBD402E46C959E1C" box="[1096,1227,1524,1549]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Pristidae" genus="Pristiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pristiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="perrotteti">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FBD402E46C959E1C" box="[1096,1227,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">P. perrotteti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FB6102E46DC29E1F" author="Gunter, G." box="[1277,1436,1524,1550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="194 - 200" refId="ref17775" refString="Gunter, G. (1941) Relative numbers of shallow water fishes of the northern Gulf of Mexico, with some records of rare fishes from the Texas coast. The American Midland Naturalist, 26 (1), 194 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2420766" type="journal article" year="1941">Gunter (1941)</bibRefCitation>
as “probably” occurring off the 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6665FFD5FD9801086A1B9E23" box="[516,581,1560,1586]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Texas</collectingRegion>
coast is likely the earliest in the scientific literature (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FB3A01086D3C9E23" author="Baughman, J. L." box="[1190,1378,1560,1586]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="43 - 48" refId="ref15359" refString="Baughman, J. L. (1943) Notes on sawfish, Pristis perotteti Muller and Henle, not previously reported from the waters of the United States. Copeia, 1943 (1), 43 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1437880" type="journal article" year="1943">Baughman 1943</bibRefCitation>
confirmed Gunter’s assertion two years later) although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FD47012C6B9B9E47" author="Burgess, G. H. &amp; Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L." box="[731,965,1596,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref16190" refString="Burgess, G. H., Carvalho, J. F. &amp; Imhoff, J. L. (2009) An evaluation of the status of the largetooth sawfish, Pristis perotteti, based on historic and recent distribution and qualitative observations of abundance. Florida Museum of Natural History Report, 2009, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="2009">
Burgess 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FCA7012C6B2A9E47" box="[827,884,1596,1622]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
list several records starting in 1917 based on images published in the popular press or included in personal correspondences.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B4E76665FFD5FF5B019468999F43" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6665FFD5FF5B01946BCF9F1B" blockId="3.[151,1437,1127,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FF5B019469659E8F" bold="true" box="[199,315,1668,1694]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Remarks.</emphasis>
A recent revision of the sawfish family (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FC9601946B999E8F" author="Faria, V. V. &amp; McDavitt, M. T. &amp; Charvet, P. &amp; Wiley, T. R. &amp; Simpfendorfer, C. A. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P." box="[778,967,1668,1694]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="136 - 164" refId="ref16966" refString="Faria, V. V., McDavitt, M. T., Charvet, P., Wiley, T. R., Simpfendorfer, C. A. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P. (2013) Species delineation and global population structure of Critically Endangered sawfishes (Pristidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 167 (1), 136 - 164 https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2012.00872. x" type="journal article" year="2013">
Faria 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FCD101946BD89E8F" box="[845,902,1668,1694]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) has indicated the three species generally considered to comprise the largetooth sawfish group are actually a single globally distributed species. Like its congener 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6665FFD5FF4701DC69039EF4" authorityName="Latham" authorityYear="1794" box="[219,349,1740,1765]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Pristidae" genus="Pristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pristiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FF4701DC69039EF4" box="[219,349,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">P. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6665FFD5FEF601DC69949EF4" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[362,458,1740,1765]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Squalidae" genus="Squalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squaliformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pristis">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FEF601DC69949EF4" box="[362,458,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">P. pristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a long and convoluted taxonomic history complicated by frequent misidentification, much of which is condensed and summarized by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6665FFD5FD2301E06BD39F1B" author="Faria, V. V. &amp; McDavitt, M. T. &amp; Charvet, P. &amp; Wiley, T. R. &amp; Simpfendorfer, C. A. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P." box="[703,909,1776,1802]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" pagination="136 - 164" refId="ref16966" refString="Faria, V. V., McDavitt, M. T., Charvet, P., Wiley, T. R., Simpfendorfer, C. A. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P. (2013) Species delineation and global population structure of Critically Endangered sawfishes (Pristidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 167 (1), 136 - 164 https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2012.00872. x" type="journal article" year="2013">
Faria 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FC9C01E06B669F1B" box="[768,824,1776,1802]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6665FFD5FF5B000368999F43" blockId="3.[151,1437,1127,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6665FFD5FF5B000369E19F3F" bold="true" box="[199,447,1811,1838]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
Critically Endangered, listed as Endangered under the 
<collectingCountry id="F32FA7FC6665FFD5FBBC00046CEB9F3F" box="[1056,1205,1812,1838]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">United States</collectingCountry>
Endangered Species Act.
</paragraph>
